genresAdvancedInfo.name: paracana
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Paracana is a genre of music that originated in Brazil and is characterized by its lively rhythms and infectious energy. It is often played on percussion instruments such as the tamborim, agogo, and surdo, and is accompanied by dance and song. Paracana is popular in both traditional and modern contexts and is often heard at carnivals and other festive occasions. Its joyful and celebratory nature makes it a favorite of audiences around the world.
